We're very capable of addressing physical wounds of war. We've gotten much better at dealing with mental wounds of war. Now, it’s time we recognize toxic wounds of war.

@JerryMoran and I wrote about how our #PACTAct finally pays the full cost of war.
https://t.co/nZjLkwC0ns

My COST of War Act ensures we're living up to the promises we've made to our veterans by expanding 
@DeptVetAffairs health care to vets of all generations suffering from the effects of toxic exposure.

These veterans earned their care, and we must deliver. That's the cost of war.
